description:
&lt;p&gt;Cwm Taf University Health Board seeks to appoint a highly motivated individual to join the CAMHS Directorate in an innovative and dynamic team based within the Swansea Bay locality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate must have the calibre to work at a fast pace, and support the Senior Nurse in leading a diverse team of nurses based within the Cwm Taf Morgannwg locality&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The applicant will have line management responsibilities, help lead on the governance agenda which would include: the management of complaints, health and safety, quality and risk. The successful candidate will also assist in professionally developing the nursing team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post-holder must be a Registered Mental Health Nurse; possess highly specialised knowledge to Degree Level; possess specialised and in-depth professional knowledge relevant to the sphere of responsibilities; have experience of working with Multi-Disciplinary and Multi-Agency Teams at an operational &amp; strategic level.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post-holder must be flexible to the service, motivated and innovative with good interpersonal skills and have the ability to communicate effectively. They will be an active member of the LMT (Locality Management Team) and contribute to the strategic vision of the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to be enthusiastic about improving services for and working directly with young people who are experiencing mental health difficulties and their families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 15th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Christina Morgan Job titleSenior Nurse&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address christina.morgan2@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 01443 443008&lt;/p&gt;
